# Apps Script Conventions

## Style

- ES5-compatible syntax (`var`, no arrow functions) — standard for `.gs` files
- Private helpers: suffix with `_` (e.g. `getQuizSpreadsheet_`, `ensureResponsesHeaders_`)
- Use `getQuizSpreadsheet_()` for all spreadsheet access (works in editor, menu, and web app)

## ID-based linking (do not regress)

Evaluation and review use **question ID** and **quiz ID**, not response row numbers:

| Sheet | Question ID | Quiz ID |
|---|---|---|
| Questions | F | E |
| QuestionImages | A | B |
| Responses | E | F |
| Evaluations | F | G |

Key helpers:

- `normalizeSheetId_(value)`, `cellText_(value)` — safe ID/text handling
- `getQuestionAndRubricByQuestionId_(questionsSheet, questionId, quizId, skipImages)` — rubric lookup; pass `true` for skipImages during grading
- `getQuestionBankForQuiz_(questionsSheet, quizId, skipImages)` — review bank; skipImages avoids loading full image data
- `findQuestionById_`, `resolveEvalRowIds_`, `lookupQuestionInBank_` — review screen
- `questionHasImageMarker_(legacyCellValue)` — fast hasImage check from column G (`PARTS:n` or `data:image/...`)
- `readQuestionImageDataForQuestion_(ss, questionId, quizId, legacyCellValue)` — targeted image read (preferred)
- `buildQuestionImageMap_`, `readQuestionImageData_`, `writeQuestionImageToSheet_` — legacy QuestionImages path (still used for old saves)
- `ensureQuestionIds_(questionsSheet)` — batch backfill F column
- `generateShortId_()` / `generateUniqueQuestionId_` / `generateUniqueQuizId_` — 8-char IDs
- `ensureLogsSheet_`, `logQuizEvent_`, `logFromClient` — **Logs** tab

## Batch evaluation helpers

- `triggerEvaluation(quizId)` — public entry; delegates to `triggerEvaluationByQuestion_`
- `buildEvaluationRunPlan_(quizId)` — collect Pending groups, build per-batch steps
- `executeEvaluationPlanStep_(plan, stepIndex, ...)` — one Anthropic batch + sheet writes
- `buildEvaluationResult_(plan, actualMs)` — return object + `logEvaluationUiEvent_('serverResultReady', ...)`
- `collectPendingResponsesByQuestion_(allResponses, quizId)` — group Pending rows by question
- `callAnthropicBatchGrade_(apiKey, question, rubric, entries)` — one API call for up to `EVAL_BATCH_SIZE_` (15) answers; **always** prepends `EVAL_GRADING_PHILOSOPHY_` (Grading for Equity 0–4 scale)
- `extractJsonFromModelText_(text)`, `formatBatchEvaluationText_(score, feedback)`, `writeBatchEvaluationResults_` (writes Evaluations + appends **EvaluationHistory** `AI` rows)
- Constants: `EVAL_BATCH_SIZE_ = 15`, `EVAL_BATCH_MAX_TOKENS_ = 8192`, `EVAL_MODEL_ = 'claude-haiku-4-5-20251001'`, `EVAL_SCORE_MAX_ = 4`, `EVAL_GRADING_PHILOSOPHY_`, `EVAL_ESTIMATE_SEC_PER_API_CALL_ = 5`, `EVAL_ESTIMATE_SEC_OVERHEAD_ = 3`
- Scores: whole numbers **0–4**; stored as `Score: X/4` in Evaluations column E
- Per-question rubrics list **requested facts**; do not use legacy `/10` point-bucket rubrics in new content

## Evaluation timing helpers

- `countEvaluationApiCalls_(questionOrder, groups)`, `estimateEvaluationDurationMs_(apiCallCount)`, `roundEvaluationSeconds_(ms)`
- `logEvaluationTiming_(phase, details)` — Logs source `evaluation`; `event: evaluationTiming`, phases `started` / `completed` / `failed`
- `logEvaluationUiEvent_(phase, details)` — Logs source `evaluationUi`
- `getLastEvaluationTimingByQuiz_()` — latest completed timing per quizId from Logs (newest first; no age limit)
- `serializeEvaluationTimingForClient_(timing)`, `serializeQuizEvaluationListForClient_(list)` — **required** before returning to web app
- `formatEvaluationDuration_(seconds)`, `formatEvaluationAlertText_(result)` — menu alert after **Run AI Evaluation**

## Public API surface (web + menu)

**Teacher**

- `addQuestionAndRubric({ quizName, question, rubric, imageData })` — single call; optional `imageData` (full data URL) saved to Questions G via `prepareQuestionImageData_`
- `getQuizEvaluationList()` — all quizzes + `pendingCount` + `lastEvaluation` (serialized; primitives only)
- `triggerEvaluation(quizId)` — question-first batch grading; omit `quizId` to grade all (menu); returns result object with `evalRunId`, `estimatedSec`, `actualSec`, etc.
- `getQuizReviewList()` — quizzes + `evaluatedCount` + `commentedCount`
- `getEvaluationsForQuiz(quizId)` — returns `hasImage`, `studentReviewText` (not `imageData`); lazy image load on client; server sorts student-first (client re-filters/re-sorts in `teacher.html` Review UI)
- `updateEvaluation(row, evaluationText)` — teacher edit of column E; appends **EvaluationHistory** (`Teacher`) when text changes
- `seedHistogramPilotQuiz()` / `seedHistogramPilotQuizWithAlert()` — 2-question pilot + 5 student responses
- `seedExtendedHistogramPilotQuiz()` / `seedExtendedHistogramPilotQuizWithAlert()` — 8-question pilot + 16 students (128 responses)
- `clearAllQuizData()` / `clearAllQuizDataWithConfirm()` — wipe Questions/Responses/Evaluations/**EvaluationHistory** data rows (headers kept); Logs preserved

**Student**

- `getQuizList()`
- `getQuestionsForQuiz(quizId)` — `{ questionId, questionText, hasImage, number }` (no image payload)
- `getQuestionImage(quizId, questionId)` — lazy image load
- `submitQuiz(studentName, quizId, answers)` — batch `setValues` on Responses
- `getStudentReviewQuizList(studentName)` — quizzes with AI evaluations for that student
- `getStudentEvaluationsForQuiz(studentName, quizId)` — one student's evaluated items (wraps `getEvaluationsForQuiz` + filter)
- `updateStudentReview(row, studentName, reviewText)` — student edit of Evaluations column H; validates name matches row

**Menu**

- `openLogsSheet`, `setupSheet`, `showAddQuestionDialog`, `runEvaluationWithAlert`, `authorizeExternalRequests`, `seedHistogramPilotQuizWithAlert`, `seedExtendedHistogramPilotQuizWithAlert`, `clearAllQuizDataWithConfirm`

**Routing**

- `doGet(e)` — default → student; `?teach` → teacher

## Image validation and storage

- `prepareQuestionImageData_(base64Image)` — strip whitespace, require `data:image/(png|gif);base64,`, max ~1 MB decoded
- **New saves:** full data URL in Questions G (works for typical quiz images ≤ ~1 MB / ~92k char data URLs)
- **Legacy:** `PARTS:n` in G + QuestionImages rows; do not break read path

Legacy upload API (`beginQuestionImageUpload`, `uploadQuestionImagePart`, `uploadQuestionImageParts`, `finalizeQuestionImageUpload`) remains in Code.gs but is **not used by current HTML UI** — do not wire back without a proven need.

## Header ensure functions

- `ensureQuestionsHeaders_` — through column G
- `ensureQuestionImagesSheet_` — QuestionImages tab (legacy)
- `ensureResponsesHeaders_` — through column F
- `ensureEvaluationsHeaders_` — through column **H** (adds **Student Review** in H if missing; migrates column E header **AI Evaluation** → **Evaluation**)
- `ensureEvaluationHistorySheet_`, `ensureEvaluationHistoryHeaders_`, `setupEvaluationHistorySheet_`, `appendEvaluationHistoryRows_` — **EvaluationHistory** tab (append-only; no web API)
- `ensureLogsSheet_` — Logs tab

## API key

```javascript
var key = PropertiesService.getScriptProperties().getProperty('ANTHROPIC_API_KEY');
```

Never commit API keys. Document Script Properties setup near `triggerEvaluationByQuestion_`.

## Common pitfalls (avoid regressions)

```javascript
// ❌ setColumnWidths does NOT accept an array
// ✅ use setColumnWidth per column in setColumnWidths_(sheet, widths)

// ❌ 4-arg getRange(row, col, row, col) is (startRow, startCol, numRows, numCols)
// ✅ use A1 notation for multi-row writes
sheet.getRange('A' + startRow + ':F' + endRow).setValues(rows);
```

- Questions `A2:G` indices: `[1]` question, `[2]` rubric, `[4]` quiz ID, `[5]` question ID, `[6]` image
- Evaluations `A2:H` indices: `[4]` current evaluation, `[5]` question ID, `[6]` quiz ID, `[7]` student review
- EvaluationHistory `A2:G` indices: `[1]` source (`AI`/`Teacher`), `[2]` student name, `[3]` question ID, `[4]` quiz ID, `[5]` Evaluations row, `[6]` evaluation text
- Call `ensureResponsesHeaders_` before reading/writing Responses
- Call `ensureEvaluationsHeaders_` before reading/writing Evaluations (including column H)
- Wrap `UrlFetchApp.fetch` + `JSON.parse` in try/catch; use `muteHttpExceptions: true`
- Pass structured payloads as **one object** to `google.script.run` (including `imageData`)
- **Do not** load full image maps in `getQuestionsForQuiz` or `getEvaluationsForQuiz` — use `hasImage` + lazy `getQuestionImage`
- **Do not** return `Date` objects (or other non-JSON types) from functions called via `google.script.run` — use `serializeQuizEvaluationListForClient_`; symptom: server logs show data but client receives empty list
- **Do not** split teacher Evaluate into multiple `google.script.run` calls per Anthropic batch unless a proven client timeout requires it — keep one `triggerEvaluation` call; batching savings are Anthropic-side only
- `clasp push` updates editor code only; web app HTML requires deployment **New version** — verify with `#buildLabel` on live pages

## OAuth scopes (appsscript.json)

Required: `spreadsheets.currentonly`, `script.external_request`
